## Calculator Usage Guide

| Input example | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `sin(30)` | sin of 30° (or 30 rad if RAD mode is on) |
| `asin(0.5)` | inverse sin → 30 (in DEG mode) |
| `log(1000)` | log base-10 → 3 |
| `ln(e)` | natural log → 1 |
| `sqrt(2)` | √2 ≈ 1.4142 |
| `cbrt(27)` | ∛27 = 3 |
| `nrt(4, 16)` | 4th root of 16 = 2 |
| `5!` | factorial(5) = 120 |
| `2^10` | 2¹⁰ = 1024 |
| `abs(-7)` | 7 |
| `floor(3.9)` | 3 |
| `ceil(3.1)` | 4 |
| `pi` | 3.14159… |
| `phi` | 1.61803… (golden ratio) |

