## Architecture Notes

```
app.py
├── inject_css()         — custom dark theme styles
├── init_state()         — session-state bootstrap
├── append_to_expr()     — expression builder
├── evaluate_expression()— safe eval with sandboxed namespace
│   ├── _preprocess()    — × → *, ! → factorial(), etc.
│   ├── _build_safe_namespace() — whitelisted math functions
│   └── _to_rad/_from_rad       — angle mode conversion
├── memory_*()           — M+, M−, MR, MC
├── render_display()     — expression + result panel
├── render_badges()      — angle mode + memory indicator
├── render_*_row()       — modular button row renderers
└── main()               — wires everything together
```

The evaluator uses Python's `eval()` with a **completely locked-down
namespace** (`__builtins__: {}`), whitelisting only the explicit set of
math functions — making it safe against code injection.